```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{chessboard}
\begin{document}
\newchessgame[id=FEN,FEN=8/8/8/8/8/8/8/1k6]
\chessboard[showmover=false,setfen=FEN]
\end{document}
```

In this example, the \newchessgame command creates a new chess game and sets the initial position using the FEN notation. The FEN notation in this case is "8/8/8/8/8/8/8/1k6", which represents a position where white has only a king on the sixth rank and black has no pieces on the board. The \chessboard command then draws the chessboard with this position. The showmover=false option removes the arrow that indicates which side is to move, and the setfen=FEN option sets the position to the one specified in the FEN notation.

